; mel-filterbank.fk — the 80-row Slaney mel filterbank as Form DATA (n_fft=400, sr=16000),
; the constant front-end weights mel-frame.fk consumes. mel-full proved the WALK on a tile;
; this fills the missing full bank so a real 80-d log-mel column computes. Each row is
; (list (list bin-indices) (list slaney-weights)); generated by the slaney triangular-filter
; formula (librosa default), baked as data like any trained weight. Proven (shape, four-way)
; by form-stdlib/tests/mel-filterbank-band.fk.

